, no surprise on mypart)--and reworking so much of it in the margin--where inspiration findsits <23> sweetest clover--that the whole had to be set anew. When the bookmade its belated appearance, as I gently aged, I might enjoy entertaining afew dear sycophantic friends in the arbor of my favorite manor of Marevo(where I had first "looked at the harlequins") with its alley of fountainsand its shimmering view of a virgin bit of Volgan steppe-land. It had to bethat way.

From my cold bed in Cambrid